Package: i3lock
Version: 2.10-1
Architecture: amd64
Maintainer: Michael Stapelberg <stapelberg@debian.org>
Installed-Size: 65
Depends: libc6 (>= 2.14), libcairo2 (>= 1.6.4-5~), libev4 (>= 1:4.04), libpam0g (>= 0.99.7.1), libxcb-image0 (>= 0.2.1), libxcb-randr0 (>= 1.12), libxcb-shm0, libxcb-util0 (>= 0.3.8), libxcb-xinerama0, libxcb-xkb1, libxcb1, libxkbcommon-x11-0 (>= 0.5.0), libxkbcommon0 (>= 0.5.0)
Section: x11
Priority: optional
Homepage: https://i3wm.org/i3lock/
Description: improved screen locker
 i3lock is a simple screen locker like slock. After starting it, you will
 see a white screen (you can configure the color/an image). You can return
 to your screen by entering your password.
 .
 i3lock forks so you can combine it with an alias to suspend to RAM.
 .
 You can specify either a background color or a PNG image which will be
 displayed while your screen is locked.
 .
 You can specify whether i3lock should bell upon a wrong password.
 .
 i3lock uses PAM and therefore is compatible with LDAP etc.
